Note.Content: MT HOTTP-B מִיֹּום RSV NRSV ESV "henceforth" NJPS "ever since day was" | NIV "from ancient days" NJB "from eternity" REB "from everlasting" = מֵעֹולָם
RSV NIV NJB NRSV REB ESV | MT NJPS "waters of Noah" = {L:מֵי<SDBH:מַיִם>}
MT HOTTP-C מִימֵי הִיא NJPS "from earliest time" | LXX "τὰ ὕδατα αὐτῆς" RSV NRSV ESV "whose waters" NIV "its waters" = {L:מֵימֶיהָ<SDBH:מַיִם>}
RSV NRSV ESV "days and years" | NIV "over a year" NJPS REB "a year or more" | NJB "the last year or two"

LEXSense.DefinitionShort: = the time of day that it is light, as opposed to the time that it is dark

= a basic unit of time, including {L:evening<SDBH:עֶרֶב>} and {L:morning<SDBH:בֹּקֶר>}; seven days make a {L:week<SDBH:שְׁבוּעָה>}; sometimes used in a figurative sense referring to a limited period of time, which may be shorter or slightly longer than a single day; the context often makes it difficult to determine
literally: days; hence: = an unspecified amount of time
literally: days; hence: = a period of a full year
literally: of days; hence: = process by which an event is repeated every year
literally: end of days; hence: = a period of time in the future
literally: as (on) this day; hence: = at this moment or as soon as possible
literally: the day of everlasting; hence: = a reference to the time of long ago
literally: days or years; hence: = a long period of time
literally: all the day; hence: = process by which an event or pattern of events takes place for an extended time, without interruption
literally: all the days; hence: = process by which an event or pattern of events takes place for an extended time, without interruption
literally: days upon days; hence, probably: = process by which a prolonged period of time elapses
literally: to days from days; exact meaning unsure; possibly: = a reference to the time after an unspecified amount of time had elapsed
literally: from days to days; hence: = process by which an event is repeated each year
= state in which a certain time span has fully elapsed
literally: to come in days; hence: = process by which humans live to an advanced age
literally: days; hence: = state in which humans have reached a relatively old age
literally: full of days; hence: = state in which humans have reached a very old age
literally: abundance of days; hence: = state in which humans have reached a very old age
literally: to be satiated with days; hence: = process by which humans live to a very old age

Glosses.Gloss: to be full (of days) > to live long

LEXSense.DefinitionShort: literally: satiated with days; hence: = state in which humans have reached a very old age
literally: ancient of days; hence: = a title for God as the one who has been in existence from everlasting
literally: words of days; hence: = a written record of events
